          "title": "CHC 101 Topic 2: The Home Care Team",
          "durationMinutes": 17,
          "content": "CHC 101 Topic 2: The Home Care Team\nThe Home Care Team\n\nCHC 101 - Introduction to Healthcare & Caregivers\n\nVisual example: Health care team discussing care together.\n\nWhen you work in home care, you are part of a team. The home care team is a group of professionals, caregivers, and sometimes family members assigned to meet the needs of one client.\n\nEach client has different needs, so each team may look a little different. Some clients need nursing care. Others need therapy, personal care, household support, or help from family caregivers.\n\nCommon team members\nPhysician or medical doctor\nRegistered nurse\nPhysical therapist\nOccupational therapist\nSpeech therapist\nSocial worker\nHome Health Aide\nHomemaker or companion\nPrimary family caregiver\nTeamwork matters\n\nGood home care depends on communication. Each team member has a role, but everyone works toward the same goal: safe, respectful, person-centered care.\n\nRemember: Home care is built on safety, respect, communication, teamwork, and following the care plan.\n\nCanvas source: https://hic.instructure.com/courses/287/pages/chc-101-topic-2-the-home-care-team?module_item_id=3002"
