          "title": "CHC 101 Topic 3: Roles of Home Care Team Members",
          "durationMinutes": 17,
          "content": "CHC 101 Topic 3: Roles of Home Care Team Members\nRoles of Home Care Team Members\n\nCHC 101 - Introduction to Healthcare & Caregivers\n\nVisual example: Medical professional reviewing care information.\n\nUnderstanding each team member’s role helps the Home Health Aide know who provides which type of care and when to ask for help.\n\nTeam Member\tRole\nPhysician\tAuthorizes treatment and oversees the plan of care.\nRegistered Nurse\tEvaluates the client, provides skilled care, and supervises aides.\nPhysical Therapist\tHelps restore movement, strength, and physical function.\nOccupational Therapist\tHelps the client improve daily living skills like dressing, bathing, and cooking.\nSocial Worker\tHelps the client and family cope and connects them with resources.\nSpeech Therapist\tHelps with speech, language, and swallowing concerns.\nQuick learner check\n\nQuestion: Who supervises the Home Health Aide in many home care settings?\nAnswer: The registered nurse.\n\nRemember: Home care is built on safety, respect, communication, teamwork, and following the care plan.\n\nCanvas source: https://hic.instructure.com/courses/287/pages/chc-101-topic-3-roles-of-home-care-team-members?module_item_id=3003"
